#: Game.Levels.SetsAndMembership.L09_IfAndOnlyIf
msgid "Before we can prove two sets are equal, we need to work with **if and\n"
"only if** (§0). The statement §1 means 'P implies Q and Q\n"
"implies P.'\n"
"\n"
"To **prove** §2, use §3 to split it into two goals:\n"
"- the forward direction §4\n"
"- the backward direction §5\n"
"\n"
"Then prove each direction separately.\n"
"\n"
"In this level, you have two hypotheses — one for each direction — and\n"
"need to combine them into an iff. This is the simplest iff proof:\n"
"split with §6, then supply each direction."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `change`
#. §1: `show`
#. §2: `change`
#. §3: `change <expression>`
#. §4: `change <expression> at h`
#. §5: `h`
#. §6: `change`
#. §7: `hx : x ∈ \\u007By | P y\\u007D`
#. §8: `change P x at hx`
#. §9: `hx : P x`
#: Game.Levels.SetsAndMembership.L02_SetBuilderNotation
msgid "The §0 tactic replaces a goal or hypothesis with a definitionally\n"
"equal expression. Unlike §1 (which only works on the goal), §2\n"
"can also modify hypotheses.\n"
"\n"
"## Syntax\n"
"- §3 — replaces the current goal\n"
"- §4 — replaces hypothesis §5\n"
"\n"
"## When to use\n"
"Use §6 when a hypothesis or goal involves set membership notation\n"
"that obscures the underlying proposition. For example, if §7,\n"
"then §8 rewrites the hypothesis to §9."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.SetsAndMembership.L09_IfAndOnlyIf
msgid "If and Only If"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `intro x hx`
#. §1: `x ∈ A`
#. §2: `have hxB := h1 hx`
#. §3: `x ∈ B`
#. §4: `exact h2 hxB`
#. §5: `x ∈ C`
#. §6: `exact h2 (h1 hx)`
#. §7: `h2 (h1 hx)`
#. §8: `A → B → C`
#: Game.Levels.SetsAndMembership.L06_SubsetTransitivity
msgid "You proved subset transitivity by chaining two subset applications.\n"
"\n"
"The pattern is clear:\n"
"\n"
"1. §0 — assume §1\n"
"2. §2 — deduce §3 from the first subset\n"
"3. §4 — deduce §5 from the second subset\n"
"\n"
"You could also compress this into a single line: §6.\n"
"The expression §7 reads as 'apply h2 to the result of\n"
"applying h1 to hx' — which is exactly the chain §8.\n"
"\n"
"This chaining pattern appears constantly in set theory proofs."
msgstr ""

#: GameServer.RpcHandlers
msgid "intermediate goal solved! 🎉"
msgstr ""

