#. §12: `h : x ∈ B`
#. §13: `specialize`
#. §14: `h : A ⊆ B`
#. §15: `hx : x ∈ A`
#. §16: `specialize`
#: Game.Levels.SetsAndMembership.L05_UsingSubsetHypotheses
msgid "In the last two levels you proved subset relationships. Now you will\n"
"*use* one.\n"
"\n"
"If you have §0 and §1, then §2 is really\n"
"a function: it takes a proof that §3 and produces a proof that\n"
"§4. You can feed it the evidence directly with §5\n"
"or with §6.\n"
"\n"
"But there is a more readable approach: the **§7** tactic.\n"
"Writing §8 replaces the hypothesis §9 in place, changing\n"
"it from §10 (which is §11) to\n"
"§12 by feeding it the specific element and its membership proof.\n"
"\n"
"**New tactic**: §13 — applies a universal hypothesis to specific\n"
"arguments, replacing the hypothesis with the resulting statement.\n"
"\n"
"In this level, you have §14 and §15. Use §16\n"
"to extract the consequence, then close the goal."
msgstr ""

