#: Game.Levels.SetsAndMembership.L01_WhatIsASet
msgid "# Sets and Membership\n"
"\n"
"Welcome to the first real world of Functions & Relations!\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, a set is not a separate type. A set of natural numbers is a\n"
"*predicate* — a function §0 that says which elements belong.\n"
"Formally, §1 is defined as §2.\n"
"\n"
"For example, the set of numbers greater than 3 is the predicate\n"
"§3. Saying '5 is in this set' just means 'the predicate\n"
"is true at 5.'\n"
"\n"
"When you see §4 in a goal, Lean is really saying §5 — the\n"
"predicate §6 applied to §7. The **§8** tactic lets you replace\n"
"the goal with a definitionally equal expression, which is perfect for\n"
"revealing what set membership really means.\n"
"\n"
"**New tactics**: §9 — replaces the goal with a definitionally equal\n"
"form. §10 — closes arithmetic goals involving natural numbers.\n"
"\n"
"In this level, your goal is §11 where §12 is the set of numbers\n"
"greater than 3. Use §13 to reveal the underlying\n"
"proposition, then close the arithmetic goal with §14."
msgstr ""

