#: Game.Levels.SetsAndMembership.L14_Boss
msgid "# Congratulations!\n"
"\n"
"You proved the antisymmetry of subset from first principles.\n"
"\n"
"Let us step back and see what happened in ordinary mathematics:\n"
"\n"
"*To show A = B, we show they have the same elements. Take any x.\n"
"If x ∈ A, then x ∈ B because A ⊆ B. If x ∈ B, then x ∈ A because\n"
"B ⊆ A. So x ∈ A ↔ x ∈ B, and since x was arbitrary, A = B.*\n"
"\n"
"Your Lean proof was a direct formalization of this argument:\n"
"- §0 — 'take any x'\n"
"- §1 — 'we show both directions'\n"
"- §2 — 'if x ∈ A then x ∈ B by h1'\n"
"- §3 — 'if x ∈ B then x ∈ A by h2'\n"
"\n"
"This **ext → constructor → chase** pattern is the most important proof\n"
"shape in this course. You will use it again and again as we move to\n"
"set operations, functions, and beyond.\n"
"\n"
"**World complete!** You now know how to:\n"
"- Prove set membership using §4 and §5\n"
"- Prove subset relationships using §6\n"
"- Use subset hypotheses with §7 or direct application\n"
"- Prove set equality using §8 (extensionality)\n"
"- Prove set equality using §9 (double inclusion)\n"
"- Work with §10 and §11\n"
"- Split and use §12 statements (with §13, §14, §15)\n"
"\n"
"Next world: **Set Operations** — where you will learn to prove\n"
"identities involving union, intersection, difference, and complement."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `A ⊆ B`
#. §1: `A`
#. §2: `B`
#. §3: `A ⊆ B`
#. §4: `∀ x, x ∈ A → x ∈ B`
#. §5: `A ⊆ B`
#. §6: `intro x hx`
#. §7: `x ∈ A`
#. §8: `x ∈ B`
#. §9: `h : A ⊆ B`
#. §10: `h hx`
#. §11: `hx : x ∈ A`
#. §12: `x ∈ B`
#. §13: `⊆`
#. §14: `⊂`
#: Game.Levels.SetsAndMembership.L03_SubsetProofs
msgid "§0 means that every element of §1 is also an element of §2.\n"
"Formally, §3 is defined as §4.\n"
"\n"
"To prove §5, use §6 to assume §7, then show §8.\n"
"To *use* §9 with a specific element, use §10 where §11\n"
"to get §12.\n"
"\n"
"Note: §13 allows equality (like ≤). Lean also has §14 for strict subset\n"
"(like <), but we will not use it in this course."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `ext x`
#. §1: `constructor`
#. §2: `intro h`
#: Game.Levels.SetsAndMembership.L11_SetExtensionality
msgid "You proved your first set equality using extensionality!\n"
"\n"
"Let us translate this into ordinary mathematics:\n"
"\n"
"*To show these two sets are equal, we show they have the same elements.\n"
"Take any x. If P(x) holds, then Q(x) holds by hypothesis h. If Q(x)\n"
"holds, then P(x) holds by hypothesis h'. So x is in the first set if\n"
"and only if it is in the second, and since x was arbitrary, the sets\n"
"are equal.*\n"
"\n"
"**The ext pattern**:\n"
"1. §0 — 'two sets are equal iff they have the same elements'\n"
"2. §1 — split the iff into forward and backward\n"
"3. §2 + prove membership — handle each direction\n"
"\n"
"In harder problems, the two directions will require different reasoning.\n"
"But the pattern stays the same."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `Set.subset_univ`
#. §1: `A ⊆ Set.univ`
#. §2: `A`
#: Game.Metadata
msgid "§0 states that §1 for any set §2. Disabled\n"
"in levels where you are learning about the universal set."
msgstr ""

